\begin_layout Subsubsection
Conversion Time
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Conversion Time 
\change_inserted 1469408620 1668157806
(
\begin_inset Formula $T_{CONV}$
\end_inset

)
\change_unchanged
is the time required by the TDC to produce a valid output measurement, given
 an input time interval.
 
\change_deleted 1469408620 1668157476
In the case of the TDC, the Conversion Time is equivalent to the length
 of the pipeline used for translating the physical time information into
 the output digital code.
\change_inserted 1469408620 1668159975
It is thus the propagation delay from the system's input to its output.
 In particular, if a pipelined TDC is used, 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{CONV}$
\end_inset

 is equal to the time needed to cross all the Pipeline stages, and, if a
 storage mechanism (e.g., a First-In First-Out structure, called FIFO) is
 also present, it is equal to the propagation delay needed to cross both
 the FIFO and the entire Pipeline.
 On the other hand,
\change_deleted 1469408620 1668157549
 
\change_inserted 1469408620 1668159978
 if a Pipeline structure is not implemented, 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{CONV}$
\end_inset

 is equal to the propagation delay needed to cross the logic blocks used
 for generating the digital code.
 Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Conversion-Time,-Maximum"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 shows the concept of Conversion Time (in blue).
\change_deleted 1469408620 1668157607

