\end_inset

 (on the right) represents the concept just explained, showing the improved
 multi-hit capability of the TDC with respect to the first two cases (on
 the left and at the center).
 In fact, the first two cases represent a situation in which the inverse
 of the incoming events' rate is lower than the minimum Dead-Time (i.e., 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{CLK}^{SLOW}$
\end_inset

), leading to the loss of a valid measurement.
 
\change_deleted 1469408620 1668162962

